==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1813|1813]], from [[Modern Latin]] genus name [[Mastodon]] ([[wp:1806|1806]]), coined by [[wp:Georges Cuvier|Georges Cuvier]], from {{Gr.}} [[mastos]], "breast" + [[-dont]], "tooth," from the similarity of the [[nipple-like]] [[projection]]s on the [[crown]]s of the [[extinct]] mammal's [[molar]]s.

===Noun===
'''mastodon''' or '''mastodont''' {{wikipedia}}

# Extinct elephant-like mammal that [[flourish]]ed worldwide from [[Miocene]] through [[Pleistocene]] times; differ from [[elephant]]s and [[mammoth]]s in the form of the molar teeth
#: ''The exhausted mine was like the body of a huge fantastically-shaped mastodon, from which all the organs of life have been taken, and only the skeleton remains.'' &mdash; [[w:The Underground City|The Underground City]] by [[w:Jules Verne|Jules Verne]]

